        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14713",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The following code produces empty arrays for the date values in the request.\n\n{code:title=standard method}\n$this->xmlrpc_client = new Zend_XmlRpc_Client($this->xmlrpc_server);\n$start = new Zend_XmlRpc_Value_DateTime(time()-1000000);\n$end = new Zend_XmlRpc_Value_DateTime(time());\n$timezone = 'Europe\/Berlin';\n\n$params   = array();\n$params[] = 'username';\n$params[] = ' password';\n$params[] = $start;\n$params[] = $end;\n$params[] = $timezone;\n\n$response = $this->xmlrpc_client->call($methos, $params);\n{code}\n\nWe found the following \"fix\" - we just don't know where the parameters are lost with the above method.\n\n{code:title=manual method}\n$this->xmlrpc_client = new Zend_XmlRpc_Client($this->xmlrpc_server);\n$start = new Zend_Date(time());\n$end = new Zend_Date(time());\n$timezone = 'Europe\/Berlin';\n\n\n$request = new Zend_XmlRpc_Request($method);\n$request->addParam($this->username);\n$request->addParam($this->password);\n$request->addParam($start,Zend_XmlRpc_Value::XMLRPC_TYPE_DATETIME);\n$request->addParam($end,Zend_XmlRpc_Value::XMLRPC_TYPE_DATETIME);\n$request->addParam($timezone);\n\n$this->xmlrpc_client->doRequest($request);\nreturn  $this->xmlrpc_client->getlastResponse();\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-22T16:01:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-22T16:01:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14720",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "With the latest from SVN. Additional tests...\n\n{code}\n$params = array();\n\n$test = array(\n                'type'  => Zend_Xmlrpc_Value::XMLRPC_TYPE_DATETIME,\n                'value' => date('Ymd\\TH:i:s)\n);\narray_push($params, $test);\n\n$myClient->call('foo.bar', $params);\n{code}\n\nNo matter, the value is a string inside the request, never of type datetime.\n\nWe also tried this:\n\n{code}\n$myClient = (...);\n$request = new Zend_XmlRpc_Request('foo.bar');\n$request->addParam(time(), Zend_XmlRpc_Value::XMLRPC_TYPE_DATETIME);\n$request->addParam(date('Ymd\\TH:i:s'), Zend_XmlRpc_Value::XMLRPC_TYPE_DATETIME);\n\n$myClient->doRequest($request);\n{code}\n\nNeither works. Both parameters are strings.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-23T07:43:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-23T07:43:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14724",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Assigning to Matthew.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-23T10:04:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-23T10:04:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14732",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Resolved in r4901. The request object was not passing the registered value type on to Zend_XmlRpc_Value, which caused each of the behaviours reported. Added test cases for both the client and request objects to verify each use case now works.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-23T10:47:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-23T10:47:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14733",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Not yet!\n\nWhen I build a value ({{$test}}), it works, the struct {{$test4}} too.\n\nAs soon as I try to stack a dateTime.iso8601 ({{$test5}}) in there it does recognize the date value. The integer, string and boolean values are guessed correct, but the date is not.\n\nIn $test5 I tried stacking {{array('type' => Zend_Xmlrpc_value::XMLRPC_TYPE_DATETIME, 'value' => date('Ymd\\Th:i:s'));}} in there, but it made type a paramter (of type \"string\") which contains \"dateTime.iso8601\" and the actual date value is a \"string\" as well. When I only supply {{'key5' => date('Ymd\\Th:i:s')}} it's just a string as well.\n\n(Sounds confusing - let me know what I can do to help.)\n\n{code}\n$myClient = (...);\n\n\/\/ works\n$test = array(\n                'type'  => Zend_Xmlrpc_Value::XMLRPC_TYPE_DATETIME,\n                'value' => date('Ymd\\TH:i:s')\n);\n\n\/\/ works\n$test4 = array(\n                    'type' => Zend_Xmlrpc_Value::XMLRPC_TYPE_STRUCT,\n                    'value' => array(\n                                    'key1' => 'Hallo Welt',\n                                    'key2' => 1,\n                                    'key3' => true,\n                                    'key4' => false\n                   )\n);\n\n\/\/ doesn't work\n$test5 = array(\n                    'type' => Zend_Xmlrpc_Value::XMLRPC_TYPE_STRUCT,\n                    'value' => array(\n                                    'key1' => 'Hallo Welt',\n                                    'key2' => 1,\n                                    'key3' => true,\n                                    'key4' => false,\n                                    'key5' => array('value' => date('Ymd\\Th:i:s'), 'type' =>  Zend_XmlRpc_Value::XMLRPC_TYPE_DATETIME)\n                   )\n);\n\n$params = array();\narray_push($params, $test);\narray_push($params, $test4);\narray_push($params, $test5);\n\n$myClient->call('foo.bar', $params);\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-23T11:44:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-23T11:44:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14734",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Btw, is it a bug or a feature - I can not pass an object (Zend_XmlRpc_Value_*) to call:\n\n{code}\n$params = array();\n\n$val = new Zend_XmlRpc_Value_DateTime('now');\n\narray_push($params, $val);\n\n$myClient = new ...;\n$myClient->call('foo.bar', $params);\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=till",
                        "name": "till",
                        "displayName": "Till Klampaeckel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-23T11:57:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-23T11:57:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14735",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The use case you present in test 5 has never been supported, and can't be. There's no way to tell a value returned by time() from an int (it *is* an int), and with the variety of string date\/time formats available, trying to autodetect would have been a nightmare.  Hence,to pass a value as a dateTime.iso8601, the only way to do so is via one of these two methods:\n\n* Create a Zend_XmlRpc_Request object, and populate it via addParam(), specifying types\n* Cast the value to a Zend_XmlRpc_Value prior to passing it as an argument to the XML-RPC client\n\nRegarding passing objects as parameters, internally, Zend_XmlRpc_Value casts objects to structs via the use of get_object_vars(). If the object has no public members, this will be an empty struct. (We cannot pass objects directly as XML-RPC has no concept of objects, only scalar and collection types.)\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-23T12:18:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-23T12:18:03.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
